city.label: Bangalore
city.description:
The shining star of the Plateau which has developed into the most modernized metropolis in India, here is everything you need to know about Bangalore:

The capital city of the Indian state of Karnataka, Bangalore has just as many names as there are facets to it. Popularly known as the Garden City and the Valley of India, Bangalore, which had been named Bengaluru in the year 2006 is one of the most important cities in India. It is most importantly known for being the country’s chief IT hub, offering services related to Information Technology to clients across the globe.

Bangalore is spread out across 1276 square kilometres of land in Southern Karnataka, and it is the third most densely populated city in India, with an ever-increasing population that sums up to well over 1 crore. The city was established in the year 1537, and throughout its history has remained an important region ruled by several dynasties, including the Cholas and the Marathas. It also holds historical significance as it was the capital city of the Kingdom.

Enjoying exclusive benefits of being the capital city of Karnataka, Bangalore is the preferred location for property investments. It is well linked to all other important cities in Karnataka via highways and well-built roads which are served by a good network of public transport. Apart from an efficient railway network that links it to the rest of India, Bangalore is also one of the few cities in India to have a rapid transit system within the city. It also has an airport that has domestic as well as international connectivity.

More about the city

Culturally speaking, Bangalore is a melting pot of various cultures, thanks to the eccentric mix of the city’s population, which includes locals as well as professionals from across the nation who are operational here. In fact, Bangalore is said to be one of the most liveable cities in India; it enjoys pleasant weather throughout the year.

A chief contributor to the economy of India, Bangalore has witnessed unparalleled economic growth, earning hundreds of billions of Rupees for the Indian economy every year through its various industries which include Information Technology services, Fast Moving Consumer Goods (FMCG) and public sector heavy industries.

Bangalore has an increasing population, most of which comprises entrepreneurs and professionals who are residing here for business and employment purposes. Owing to the influx of resident population, real estate in Bangalore has been high in demand ever since the city made it to the forefront of India’s metropolitan cities.

Villages in Bangalore

Bangalore can broadly be divided into two districts – urban and rural Bangalore. The urban district covers four taluks within it, namely North, East West and South and Anekal. Some of the important villages in urban Bangalore include a, Bagalur and Ajjanahalli. On the other hand, Rural includes taluks like Devanahalli, Hoskote, a and Nelamangala. Some of the important villages in rural Bangalore are Kodihalli, Akkur, hara Vaddahalli, Honganur and Acharlahalli.

Schools and Colleges

Bangalore is a renowned educational hub not just in Karnataka but across India, and it also has some reputed world-class learning institutions operating from within the city. These include schools as well as colleges and universities. Historically, Bangalore was also a centre for religious education.

Some of the noteworthy schools in Bangalore include Bishop Cotton Boys’ School, Baldwin Girls’ High School, National Public School, Bethany High School, Kendriya Vidyalaya and St. Germain High School

One of Bangalore’s most famous educational institutions is the University, which has two colleges within the city and offers affiliation to more than 500 other colleges. There are also several other educational academies that operate from within the city including Indian Institute of gement, Institute of Technology, University Visvesvaraya College of Engineering, B College of Engineering, Medical College and Oxford Engineering College.

Shopping Malls and Recreation

Being a highly urbanized settlement, there are endless avenues for recreation that exist within the city. You will find malls and shopping centres across all parts of Bangalore, and there are several art galleries, theatres and auditoriums that host various types of events throughout the year.

Some of the popular shopping malls in Bangalore include MarketCity , Mall, Square, Garuda Mall, Lido Mall and UB City Mall.

Bangalore is also famous for its buzzing nightlife and music scene, and there are several bars and pubs located along the city’s streets.

Real Estate in Bangalore

Property in Bangalore is the most sought-after investment option in Karnataka, and several reputed builders have come up with benchmark projects across the city over the past two decades. Being the capital city, Bangalore enjoys exclusive location benefits, which have brought it to the forefront of real estate in India. In fact, the vibrant metropolis finds its place among the top cities for making real estate investments in India.

Property rates in Bangalore have risen by upto 116.7% in last 6 months.

Some of the recently launched projects in Bangalore, that you might be interested in, are Coronet Greens Apartment, Park Avenue, Paradise.

locality.label: Hennur
locality.description:
Hennur is an area located in northern part of Bangalore. It is 11.4 kilometers away from Bangalore city via Road and belongs to Bangalore division. It is enclosed by HRBR layouts, Kacharakanahalli, Hormavu and Agara. Once a sleepy village with narrow roads and congested areas, it has now transformed into an active landmark for real estate development with new infrastructural developments. Some of the nearby localities are Kalayn Nagar (3.7 Km), Horamavu (3.8Km) and Banaswadi (5.4 Km).

Connectivity

Being located in the northern extremes of the city, Hennur provides smooth connectivity to other major locations in Bangalore. The Road is only 2.8 Kilometer away and connects the locality to HAL International Airport. The HAL International Airport is 14.5 Kms away from Hennur via Outer Ring Road. The nearest railway station is Banaswadi railway station which is 7.6 kilometers away from the region and City Junction railway station is 20.7 kilometers away.

In addition to these, Road is planned to be widened to a four-lane highway along with a cargo road for the International Airport.

Educational Institutions and Hospitals

Hennur is surrounded by many educational institutions and hospitals. Some good schools in the area are High School, YuvaLok Riha Community School, Sinclars High School and Govt Lower Primary School. The list of colleges includes Hasanath Pre University College, NICC - International College of Media & Design, AMODH D.ED College and City College.

The hospitals providing medical facilities to the residents of Hennur are Shree alakshmi Hospital and Trauma Centre, Divine Hospital, Avian Hospitals, Vasan Eye Care and Feran Hospital.

Shopping Malls and Recreation

Hennur is one of the fastest developing areas of Bangalore with quite a number of shopping malls including the popular Mall and Orion Mall. For recreational purposes, the clubs close to Hennur are Country Club India Limited and Rotary Club of Cantonment. Amruth is the nearest cinema hall. Sundar Hospital and Elizabeth Manor wedding hall are other prominent landmarks. Located along Hebbal, Hennur has garnered plenty of tourist attraction of late on account of the Lake.

Real Estate in Hennur

With many new developments in the area, Hennur witnesses a higher supply of properties in premium segment. Currently, there are 31 ongoing real estate projects in Hennur and 11 projects are due for possession in 2014. Spring Nest by D S Max, Karle Town Centre Zenith BY , Paradise by Enterprises and Springdale by DS Max are some ongoing projects in Hennur and are at various stages of construction.

The average property price in Hennur is Rs. 4,400 per sq.ft., minimum property price is Rs. 3,400 per sq.ft. and maximum property price is Rs. 8,500 per sq.ft. Planned developments, proximity to the city centre and vicinity to the airport is expected to give the locality new dimensions in the coming years. With this, the real estate prices in Hennur are also expected to go up by 15 to 20 percent in coming years.
